#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.58"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.58:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.58:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "6. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.58:0.3"
msgid "58. Tikaṇṇasutta"
msgstr "58. Tikaṇṇa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.163"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tikaṇṇo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Then Tikaṇṇa the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with "
"him."

msgctxt "an3.58:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekamantaṃ nisinno kho tikaṇṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavato sammukhā tevijjānaṃ sudaṃ "
"brāhmaṇānaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati:"
msgstr ""
"Seated to one side Tikaṇṇa, in front of the Buddha, praised the brahmins who "
"were expert in the three Vedas."

msgctxt "an3.58:1.3"
msgid "“evampi tevijjā brāhmaṇā, itipi tevijjā brāhmaṇā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Such are the brahmins, masters of the three Vedic knowledges! Thus are the "
"brahmins, masters of the three Vedic knowledges!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ tevijjaṃ paññāpentī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But brahmin, how do the brahmins describe a brahmin who is master of the "
"three Vedic knowledges?”"

msgctxt "an3.58:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, "
"saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā, akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho "
"jātivādena, ajjhāyako, mantadharo, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū "
"sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, "
"veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayoti."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, it’s when a brahmin is well born on both his mother’s and "
"father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of "
"ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. He recites and remembers "
"the hymns, and is an expert in the three Vedas, together with their "
"vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. "
"He knows philology and grammar, and is well versed in cosmology and the "
"marks of a great man."

msgctxt "an3.58:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ tevijjaṃ paññāpentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how the brahmins describe a brahmin who is master of the three Vedic "
"knowledges.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Aññathā kho, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ tevijjaṃ paññāpenti, aññathā ca "
"pana ariyassa vinaye tevijjo hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, a master of three knowledges according to the brahmins is quite "
"different from a master of the three knowledges in the training of the noble "
"one.”"

msgctxt "an3.58:3.2"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye tevijjo hoti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Master Gotama, how is one a master of the three knowledges in the "
"training of the noble one?"

msgctxt "an3.58:3.3"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye tevijjo "
"hotī”ti."
msgstr "Master Gotama, please teach me this.”"

msgctxt "an3.58:3.4"
msgid "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an3.58:3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho tikaṇṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes sir,” Tikaṇṇa replied."

msgctxt "an3.58:3.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.164"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, it’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, "
"secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first "
"absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing "
"the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "an3.58:4.2"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "an3.58:4.3"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "an3.58:4.4"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness "
"and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:5.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they "
"extend it toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "an3.58:5.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi "
"jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi "
"jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattārīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi "
"jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi "
"vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto "
"evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato "
"cuto amutra udapādiṃ. Tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. "
"Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"They recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, "
"five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred "
"thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the "
"world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. They "
"remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, "
"and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was "
"how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere "
"else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, "
"and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was "
"how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ "
"And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details."

msgctxt "an3.58:5.3"
msgid "Ayamassa paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā hoti;"
msgstr "This is the first knowledge that they attain."

msgctxt "an3.58:5.4"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance is destroyed and knowledge has arisen; darkness is destroyed and "
"light has arisen, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and "
"resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.165"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:6.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they "
"extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings."

msgctxt "an3.58:6.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāti: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā … pe … "
"manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā "
"micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena "
"samannāgatā, vacīsucaritena samannāgatā, manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ "
"anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe "
"dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn "
"according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings, alas, did bad things by way of "
"body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong "
"view; and they acted out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, "
"after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, "
"hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, "
"and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and "
"they acted out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, "
"they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance "
"that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and "
"being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a "
"bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their "
"deeds."

msgctxt "an3.58:6.3"
msgid "Ayamassa dutiyā vijjā adhigatā hoti;"
msgstr "This is the second knowledge that they attain."

msgctxt "an3.58:6.4"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance is destroyed and knowledge has arisen; darkness is destroyed and "
"light has arisen, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and "
"resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:7.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they "
"extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice "
"that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati;"
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.5"
msgid "vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

msgctxt "an3.58:7.7"
msgid "Ayamassa tatiyā vijjā adhigatā hoti;"
msgstr "This is the third knowledge that they attain."

msgctxt "an3.58:7.8"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharatoti."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance is destroyed and knowledge has arisen; darkness is destroyed, and "
"light has arisen, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and "
"resolute.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:8.1"
msgid "Anuccāvacasīlassa,"
msgstr "“For someone whose ethical conduct doesn’t waver,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:8.2"
msgid "nipakassa ca jhāyino;"
msgstr "who is self-disciplined, practicing absorption;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:8.3"
msgid "Cittaṃ yassa vasībhūtaṃ,"
msgstr "whose mind is mastered,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:8.4"
msgid "ekaggaṃ susamāhitaṃ."
msgstr "unified, serene."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:9.1"
msgid "Taṃ ve tamonudaṃ dhīraṃ,"
msgstr "That wise one dispels the darkness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:9.2"
msgid "tevijjaṃ maccuhāyinaṃ;"
msgstr "master of the three knowledges, destroyer of death."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:9.3"
msgid "Hitaṃ devamanussānaṃ,"
msgstr "For the welfare of gods and humans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:9.4"
msgid "āhu sabbappahāyinaṃ."
msgstr "he’s given up everything, they say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:10.1"
msgid "Tīhi vijjāhi sampannaṃ,"
msgstr "Accomplished in the three knowledges,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:10.2"
msgid "asammūḷhavihārinaṃ;"
msgstr "living without confusion,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: antimadehinaṃ → antimasārīraṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | antimasarīraṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.58:10.3"
msgid "Buddhaṃ antimadehinaṃ,"
msgstr "bearing the final body,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:10.4"
msgid "taṃ namassanti gotamaṃ."
msgstr "they revere the awakened Gotama."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:11.1"
msgid "Pubbenivāsaṃ yo vedī,"
msgstr "Who knows their past lives,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:11.2"
msgid "saggāpāyañca passati;"
msgstr "and sees heaven and places of loss,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:11.3"
msgid "Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto,"
msgstr "and has attained the end of rebirth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:11.4"
msgid "abhiññāvosito muni."
msgstr "that sage has perfect insight."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:12.1"
msgid "Etāhi tīhi vijjāhi,"
msgstr "It’s because of these three knowledges"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:12.2"
msgid "tevijjo hoti brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr "that a brahmin is a master of the three knowledges."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:12.3"
msgid "Tamahaṃ vadāmi tevijjaṃ,"
msgstr "That’s who I call a three-knowledge master,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.58:12.4"
msgid "nāññaṃ lapitalāpananti."
msgstr "and not the other one, the lip-reciter.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.166"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:13.1"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, ariyassa vinaye tevijjo hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This, brahmin, is a master of the three knowledges in the training of the "
"noble one.”"

msgctxt "an3.58:13.2"
msgid ""
"“Aññathā, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ tevijjo, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye "
"tevijjo hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, a master of three knowledges according to the brahmins is "
"quite different from a master of the three knowledges in the training of the "
"noble one."

msgctxt "an3.58:13.3"
msgid ""
"Imassa ca pana, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye tevijjassa brāhmaṇānaṃ tevijjo "
"kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasiṃ."
msgstr ""
"And, Master Gotama, a master of three knowledges according to the brahmins "
"is not worth a sixteenth part of a master of the three knowledges in the "
"training of the noble one."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an3.58:14.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "an3.58:14.2"
msgid ""
"upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.58:14.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
